cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE

This paper presents a streaming model for large-scale classification, which involves learning and computational geometry. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of online stochastic gradient updates, which suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper mentions experimental results in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), indicating potential applications in these areas. Finally, the use of SVMs suggests a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
